# Component Style Preservation

## Context
- When modifying project structure or refactoring components
- When moving components between directories
- When updating imports or dependencies

## Critical Rules
- NEVER change existing component styles during refactoring
- Keep all existing className strings exactly as they are
- Preserve all Tailwind CSS classes in their original order
- Maintain all existing style-related props (sx, style, etc.)
- Keep all existing CSS modules imports and usage
- Preserve all existing theme configurations
- Do not modify or remove any existing style-related imports

## Examples

<example>
// Original component
<div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gray-50">
  <div className="max-w-md w-full space-y-8 p-8 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
    {children}
  </div>
</div>

// Correct refactoring - styles preserved
<div className="min-h-screen flex items-center justify-center bg-gray-50">
  <div className="max-w-md w-full space-y-8 p-8 bg-white rounded-lg shadow">
    {children}
  </div>
</div>
</example>

